# This repo tracks the PROCESS (scripts + docs), never image data. Raw frames,
# FITS/XISF intermediates, and stacked products are large and live OFF-REPO
# (backed up separately). Only per-dataset STATE (small JSON under
# datasets/<session>/<set>/) is versioned — see datasets/README.md.

# --- image data: raw frames, intermediates, products (any dir) ---
*.dng
*.DNG
*.nef
*.NEF
*.cr2
*.CR2
*.cr3
*.CR3
*.arw
*.ARW
*.raf
*.RAF
*.fit
*.fits
*.fts
*.xisf
*.ser
*.seq
*.tif
*.tiff
**/work/
**/results/

# --- anomaly-audit scratch ---
# audit_work/ (under datasets/<session>/<set>/) holds transient Siril working
# files — residual TIFFs, star lists, the .ssf, extracted-green FITS. ONLY the
# anomaly_audit.json record it contains is versioned; the rest is regenerated.
**/audit_work/*
!**/audit_work/anomaly_audit.json

# --- QA / calibration scratch ---
# qa_work/ (under datasets/<session>/<set>/) holds transient Siril working files
# (CFA FITS / .seq / .ssf / previews / logs). Only its .json records are versioned
# (frame_metrics.json, skyflat_qa.json, …); the rest is regenerated.
**/qa_work/*
!**/qa_work/*.json

# --- session data dirs ---
# Each acquisition session is a dir at the repo root, keyed <session>/, holding
# raw lights + calibration + intermediates. It is NEVER committed. The image
# patterns above already catch the frames; add the session dir itself here to
# keep stray files (previews, notes) out too, e.g.:
#   /2026-08-orion/
#
# THIRD-PARTY practice corpora especially must never be committed or
# redistributed — download and PROCESS only, link the source (terms vary: some
# are CC-BY-NC-SA / no-redistribute). Record each one's source + license in its
# exclude comment when you add it.
/july14/

# --- tooling / OS cruft ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store

# --- root-level images are working screenshots (judgment surfaces), never data ---
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
